\f0\fs24 \cf0 \cb1 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 PTSD\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl340\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs30 \cf2 \cb3 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
PTSD is a disorder that develops in some people who have experienced a shocking, scary, or dangerous event.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \cb3 It is natural to feel afraid during and after a traumatic situation. Fear triggers many split-second changes in the body to help defend against danger or to avoid it. This \'93fight-or-flight\'94 response is a typical reaction meant to protect a person from harm. Nearly everyone will experience a range of reactions after trauma, yet most people recover from initial symptoms naturally. Those who continue to experience problems may be diagnosed with PTSD. \
\
People who have PTSD may feel stressed or frightened even when they are not in danger.
